text.tspan: Wealth Manager
Platform / Specific Product
Partnerships / Notes
Types of Products & Investment Minimums
Ameriprise
Advisor-distributed alternative investments (no single
branded alts platform)
Alternatives sourced via fund sponsors; distributed through Ameriprise
advisors.
Hedge funds, private equity, real assets, structured products.
Minimums typically $100K–$250K+ per fund (varies). Public details are
limited; positioned for accredited HNW clients.
Bank of America
Merrill & Bank of America Private Bank – Alternative
Investments Platform
Alternatives platform within Merrill Wealth Management and BoA
Private Bank; distributes third-party and proprietary funds via advisor
channels.
Private equity, hedge funds, private credit, and real assets available to
accredited HNW clients through feeder/tender funds. Minimums
typically $100K–$250K.
BNY
BNY Pershing’s Alts Bridge, integrated with Wove
advisory platform (also connected to NetX360+).
Alliance with iCapital so that clients can access iCapital-managed funds
& tools via Alts Bridge and Wove; Alts Bridge also draws from a curated
set of at least 25 asset managers.
Private equity, private credit, real assets, hedge funds via feeder /
tender funds; Product-specific minimums likely vary; Targeted at
affluent/HNW clients via advisors (not UHNW bespoke mandates).
Charles Schwab
Schwab Alternative Investments Select
Works with iCapital and third-party fund managers. Access limited to
qualifying Schwab households.
Private equity, private credit, hedge funds, real estate funds. Requires
>$5M in household assets at Schwab to qualify; product minimums
typically $100K–$250K. Clearly positioned at upper-HNW, but below
UHNW.
Citigroup
Citi Wealth / Citi Private Bank – Alts Feeder Platform
(operations sold to iCapital)
iCapital now operates Citi’s former feeder-fund platform (>180 funds);
Citi continues distribution via advisors.
Private equity, private credit, venture capital, real assets via
feeder/tender funds. Minimums $100K–$250K typical. Affluent/HNW
access; separate UHNW offerings exist but not included here.
Goldman Sachs
GSAM Alternatives / G-Series Funds
Uses in-house GSAM alternatives plus external managers; partnership
with T. Rowe Price to expand access into retirement plans.
Evergreen/tender funds for HNW clients, private credit, private equity,
real assets. Minimums usually $25K–$100K+ depending on share
class. G-Series designed for accredited HNW.
JPMorgan
Chase Private Client / J.P. Morgan Private Markets Fund
Developed in-house by J.P. Morgan Asset Management.
Semi-liquid ’40-Act tender fund with quarterly liquidity. $25K minimum
investment. One of the lowest entry points for alts among big banks for
clients.
LPL Financial
LPL Alts Connect
Digital alts marketplace sourcing funds from third-party managers
(integrated via partnerships such as iCapital).
Private equity, private credit, real estate, hedge funds. Minimums
product-specific, typically $50K–$250K. Built to serve HNW clients via
independent advisor channel.
Northern Trust
Northern Trust Wealth Management (advisor-led
platform)
Leverages 50 South Capital (Northern Trust’s wholly owned alternatives
arm) to source and manage multi-manager strategies, alongside select
third-party funds. Earlier partnership with Artivest helped digitize alts
distribution for advisors.
Multi-manager and feeder funds across private equity, hedge funds,
private credit, and real assets. Typical minimums $100K–$250K per
fund. Focused on accredited HNW clients (generally below $10M net
worth).
Raymond James
Alternative Investments Group (advisor channel)
Works with third-party fund managers; distributed via Raymond James
advisors.
Hedge funds, private equity, real estate, private credit. Minimums vary
widely ($100K–$250K+). Focus is accredited HNW.
Robinhood
No HNW-ready private markets platform yet
Exploring tokenization / policy advocacy; no live products for HNW or
mass affluent as of 2025.
N/A. No current private markets offering for HNW clients.
UBS
UBS Unified Global Alternatives initiative
Longstanding partnership with iCapital; iCapital acquired UBS’s U.S.
feeder-fund platform in 2022.
Private equity, private debt, hedge funds, real assets distributed
through advisors. Minimums typically $100K–$250K. HNW accessible
via feeder funds.
US Bancorp
U.S. Bank Private Wealth Management
Offers alternatives through advisor programs.
Private equity, hedge funds, private credit, real estate via feeder funds.
Minimums not always public, typically $100K+. Serves accredited HNW.
Wells Fargo
Wells Fargo WIM alts shelf
iCapital acquired Wells Fargo’s feeder-fund platform; Wells Fargo
advisors still distribute alts through WIM and UMA programs.
Private equity, hedge funds, private credit via feeder/tender funds.
Minimums usually $100K–$250K for HNW.
Democratizing Private Markets Access: Affluent/High Net Worth (HNW) Segment
